        //// Handling unsupported properties
    > Not all browser support all HTML5 tags 
    > Not all browsers support all CSS3 properties
    >Browser prefixes (or vendor prefixes) provide a quick fix for handling 

            /*Browser Prefixes */
    chrome   => -webkit-:  >> for all the google browser IOS, Safari< Andriod
    Opera    => -o-
    mozilla   => -moz
    Internet Explorer => -ms-:


            /*Often Unsupported Properties*/
    => column-count
    => border-radius
    => gradient
    => Sites such as http://caniuse.com/ will tell you when you need to use prefixes 


     

